<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-134-574  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 134 574.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ACM Transactions on Database Systems  Dec 1989 v14 n4 p480(23).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Integrity = validity + completeness. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Motro, Amihai.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Database integrity consists of both validity, which insuresexclusion of all false information, and completeness, whichinsures inclusion of all true information.andP;  A uniform model ofintegrity for relational databases is presented that includes theprevailing model of integrity constraints to a great degree.andO;Under the new model, the integrity of answers issued by thedatabase in response to user queries is determined, making theanswers more meaningful.andP;  The model is defined and discussed andthe mechanism that implements the model is presented.andP;  Themechanism makes determination of the integrity of the answeranalogous to determining the answer.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Data BasesData IntegrityData SecurityQuery ProcessingData Base Management Systems.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   The universe of all possible tuples U, the real world W and adatabase D. (chart)A valid view V and a complete view C. (chart)Violations of constraints. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>